 behandeln. Es zeigt, wie Provenienzforschung in die Organisation integriert werden kann, wie betroffene Bücher sowie die rechtmäßigen EigentümerInnen identifiziert werden können, wie die einzelnen Fälle und Exemplare bearbeitet werden und wie wichtig dabei die Verbreitung der Forschungsergebnisse und die Vernetzung mit anderen ist.  aThis book educates library staff on how to efficiently determine whether publications that are being processed as new acquisitions or in retrospective cataloguing were or could have been plundered during the Nazi period. Spreading today's knowledge about Nazi-era provenance research will be of great importance in coming years as specific research projects come to an end and the expertise of research staff risks being lost.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aBook thefts. 0aBooksxProvenancexResearch. 0aCultural propertyxRepatriationzAustria. 0aCultural propertyxRepatriationzGermany. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)xReparations. 0aJewish property. 0aLibrarieszAustria. 0aLibrarieszGermany 0aLibrarieszGermany. 4aBibliotheksgeschichte. 4aProvenienzforschung. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh  aProvenance research.  alibrary history.1 aBauer, Bruno, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aStumpf, Markus, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Library and Information Science 2016z9783110485240oZDB-23-